snippet.textDisplay:
My favorite soup: Vegan Spinach and Ginger
5 cups baby spinach
1 large russet potato diced
1 medium onion diced
4 cups vegetable stock
about 3/4 in ginger root minced
white pepper to taste
group clove (eyeball I never measure this haha)
saute onions and ginger, add rest of ingredients (save a few spinach leaves for a garnish) bring to boil, boil until all the spinach wilts enough to be submerged in the stock, cover with lid and simmer until potatoes are soft. remove from heat, put mixture into blender and blend until smooth. pour mixture back into pot and reheat. serve hot and garnish with julienned spinach leaf. I like to eat mine with pepper jack grilled cheese <3
